HEADWORD: Unfrock
<hw>Un*frock"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>frock</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive or divest or a
frock; specifically, to deprive of priestly character or privilege;
<as>as, to <ex>unfrock</ex> a priest</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

